  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Attention Mechanism
Category:    Mechanism
Definition:  Learns to focus on relevant input parts for each output
Year:        2015
Researchers: Bahdanau et al.
Applications:Machine translation, NLP, summarization
Related:     Self-attention, multi-head, cross-attention

Concept:     LSTM
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Gating mechanisms solve vanishing gradient in sequences
Year:        1997
Researchers: Hochreiter/Schmidhuber
Applications:NLP, speech, time series
Related:     GRU, RNN, gates, cell state

Concept:     Diffusion Model
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Learns to reverse a noise-adding process for generation
Year:        2020
Researchers: Ho et al.
Applications:Image/video/audio generation (Stable Diffusion)
Related:     DDPM, score matching, noise schedule

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

Concept:    Gini Coefficient
Category:   Statistics
Definition: Measures income inequality from 0 (equal) to 1 (one person has all)
Formula:    G = 1 - 2∫L(x)dx
Economist:  Corrado Gini
Example:    USA Gini ~0.41; Denmark ~0.29; South Africa ~0.63

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

